Now the only remaining failures are from the **generated `ApiClient.java`**, not from your `PingUserClient`.

Your project uses Spring Framework 7, but the generated client still uses APIs removed in Spring 7:

```text
HttpHeaders.containsKey(...)
HttpHeaders.entrySet(...)
UriComponentsBuilder.fromHttpUrl(...)
```

Spring 7 replacements are:

```text
containsKey(...)  -> containsHeader(...)
entrySet()        -> headerSet()
fromHttpUrl(...)  -> fromUriString(...)
```

Spring Framework 7 changed `HttpHeaders` so it no longer exposes the old `Map` methods, which matches the errors in your screenshot. ([Home][1])

